NAME
    SQL::Tidy - parse and prettify SQL text

SYNOPSIS
        use SQL::Tidy;
        my $sqlt   = SQL::Tidy->new(
            indent    => 4,
        );
        my $sql = $sqlt->parse($SQL);

DESCRIPTION
    Parses SQL text and reformats it nicely indented.

CONSTRUCTOR
    The "new()" constructor takes the following arguments:

    indent (scalar, default is four ' ' spaces)
        How to indent each sub-level by when tidying.

    preserve_leading (boolean, default is true)
        Set to keep same overall indent as original.

    uppercase (boolean, default is true)
        Set to uppercase SQL keywords when tidying.

ATTRIBUTES
METHODS
    parse($sql) -> $tidy_sql
        Takes the input SQL text to be parsed and returns a tidy
        version.

